    var foo_value = get_foo_from_id(id)
    print(foo_value) # Prints bar
```

This code defines a function `get_foo_from_id` that retrieves a node's `foo` property using its instance ID. The `_ready` function tests this by printing the `foo` property of the current node.

Here's a C# function that retrieves a node using its instance ID and returns the value of the `Foo` property:

```csharp
using Godot;

public partial class MyNode : Node
{
    public string Foo { get; set; } = "bar";

    public string GetFooFromId(ulong instanceId)
    {
        var inst = (MyNode)InstanceFromId(instanceId);
        if (inst != null)
        {
            return inst.Foo;
        }
        return "";
    }

    public override void _Ready()
    {
