Here’s an implementation of a utility class in C# for encoding byte arrays to hexadecimal strings:

```csharp
public static class HexUtility
{
    // Converts a byte array to a hexadecimal string
    public static string HexEncode(byte[] bytes)
    {
        if (bytes == null || bytes.Length == 0)
            return ""; // Handle null or empty byte array

        var hexChars = new char[bytes.Length * 2];
        for (int i = 0; i < bytes.Length; i++)
        {
            int value = bytes[i];
            hexChars[i * 2] = GetHexDigit(value / 16);
            hexChars[i * 2 + 1] = GetHexDigit(value % 16);
        }
        return new string(hexChars);
    }

    private static char GetHexDigit(int value)
    {
        return (char)(value < 10 ? '0' + value : 'a' + value - 10);
    }
}

// Usage example:
var array = new byte[] {11, 46, 255};
GD.Print(HexUtility.HexEncode(array)); // Prints: 0b2eff
```

This utility class provides a safe way to convert byte arrays into hexadecimal strings, including error handling for null or empty input.

