Here's how to set and get inertia for a RigidBody2D in Godot using C#:

```csharp
private RigidBody2D _ball;

public override void _Ready()
{
    _ball = GetNode<RigidBody2D>("Ball");
    SetBallInertia(2.0f);  // Set custom inertia
}

private void SetBallInertia(float value)
{
    _ball.SetInertia(value); // Set the inertia to the given value
}

private float GetBallInertia()
{
    return 1.0f / PhysicsServer2D.BodyGetDirectState(_ball.GetRid()).InverseInertia; // Retrieve the inertia value
}
```

This code initializes a RigidBody2D node, sets a custom inertia value, and provides a method to retrieve the computed inertia based on the RigidBody2D's state. Note that if you set inertia to `0`, it will automatically compute the inertia based on the body's mass and shapes.

