Here’s how to robustly handle putting a UTF-8 string in a data stream with error handling:

```csharp
void SafePutUtf8String(string value)
{
    try
    {
        // Check for null or empty value
        if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(value))
            throw new ArgumentException("Value cannot be null or empty.");

        // Convert string to UTF-8 bytes
        byte[] utf8Bytes = value.ToUtf8Buffer();
        uint size = (uint)utf8Bytes.Length;

        // Store size
        stream.PutData(BitConverter.GetBytes(size));
        // Store actual string bytes
        stream.PutData(utf8Bytes);
    }
    catch (Exception ex)
    {
        GD.PrintErr("Error putting UTF-8 string to stream: " + ex.Message);
    }
}

// Usage example:
SafePutUtf8String("Hello World");
```

This method ensures that any issues during the string preparation or transmission are caught and logged, improving the reliability of your data handling.

