random_function()
var time_end = Time.get_ticks_usec()
print("random_function() took %d microseconds" % (time_end - time_start))
```This helps you to optimize code by identifying slow sections.

Minimizing bottlenecks in GDScript performance is crucial because it leads to smoother gameplay, better frame rates, and an overall improved user experience. By effectively profiling your code and optimizing slower functions, you ensure that your game can handle more complexity without running into performance issues. For instance, identifying a slow function with:```gdscript
var time_start = Time.get_ticks_usec()
your_slow_function()
var time_end = Time.get_ticks_usec()
print("your_slow_function() took %d microseconds" % (time_end - time_start))
```allows you to focus on optimization efforts.

