Exported variables should generally not be preloaded because they can be overwritten by the scene instantiation code. If an exported variable is preloaded, its preloaded value will be discarded when the variable is set through the editor. It's preferable to initialize exported variables with `null`, empty, or otherwise invalid default values. Example:

```gdscript
