In 3D polygon collision detection, a separating plane is used to determine if two polygons are colliding. It indicates that if all vertices of polygon A are on one side of the plane and all vertices of polygon B are on the other side, then the polygons are not overlapping. Here is how to implement checking for a separating plane in csharp:
```csharp
var overlapping = true;
foreach (Plane plane in planesOfA)
{
