    foreach (Vector3 point in pointsOfB)
    {
        if (plane.DistanceTo(point) < 0)
        {
            allOut = false;
            break;
        }
    }
    if (allOut)
    {
        overlapping = false;
        break;
    }
}
```
This code snippet checks if any plane from polygon A separates it from all points of polygon B.

To detect overlapping 3D polygons, you'll need to iteratively check separating planes. Here’s a basic implementation:
